// ============================================================================
// DEVELOPMENT NOTES
// ============================================================================
// 
// 1. SECURITY BEST PRACTICES:
//    - Never hardcode API keys in source code
//    - Never commit API keys to version control
//    - Use environment-specific configurations
//    - Rotate keys regularly
//
// 2. HOW THIS WORKS:
//    - This .xcconfig file sets build-time variables
//    - Variables are injected into Info.plist during build
//    - SecureAPIConfig reads from Info.plist and Keychain
//    - Keys are automatically stored in Keychain for security
//
// 3. MULTIPLE ENVIRONMENTS:
//    You can create environment-specific config files:
//    - Config-Development.xcconfig
//    - Config-Production.xcconfig
//    - Config-Staging.xcconfig
//
// 4. TESTING:
//    For testing without real keys, use:
